body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/449\n\n## Problem (contract drift)\n`pm contracts --json` advertises extension_contracts.policy_modes = [\"off\",\"warn\",\"enforce\"] (same for trust_modes), but governance config keys (e.g. governance-workflow-enforcement) accept `strict`, not `enforce`. Agents driving config from contracts construct invalid writes — exactly the drift class pm contracts exists to prevent.\n\n## Proposed fix\nSingle source of truth for mode tokens shared by contracts and config validation; either rename config token to `enforce` (with alias) or fix contracts to advertise `strict`; add a drift spec that walks advertised enum tokens through the real validators.\n\n## Definition of done\nAdvertised policy/trust mode tokens are accepted verbatim by config set; drift spec pins contracts<->validator parity; contracts:update run."
